chronitem.event:
John F. (Del) Sawyer, Director of the Blair Academy, asks Alfred to write a composition for chorus and orchestra for the Nashville Youth Symphony featuring a favorite poem of Valere Blair Potter titled
            And Well I Shall Be There;
            it is later performed at the War Memorial in Nashville by the Nashville Youth Symphony and McGavock High School Chorus, conducted by Jay Dawson

The transcription/arrangement of Bartok’s
            First Rhapsody
            for violin/cello premieres at the Sewanee Summer Music Festival (Paul York, cellist)

